 <h1 class=\"firstHeading\" id=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">\n    Erlembald\n   </h1>\n   <div class=\"mw-body-content\" id=\"bodyContent\">\n    <div class=\"noprint\" id=\"siteSub\">\n     From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia\n    </div>\n    <div id=\"contentSub\">\n    </div>\n    <div id=\"contentSub2\">\n    </div>\n    <div id=\"jump-to-nav\">\n    </div>\n    <a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#mw-head\">\n     Jump to navigation\n    </a>\n    <a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#searchInput\">\n     Jump to search\n    </a>\n    <div class=\"mw-content-ltr\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\">\n     <div class=\"mw-parser-output\">\n      <div class=\"thumb tright\">\n       <div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\">\n        <a class=\"image\" href=\"/wiki/File:0317_-_Milano_-_San_Calimero_-_Foto_Giovanni_Dall%27Orto_5-May-2007.jpg\">\n         <img alt=\"\" class=\"thumbimage\" data-file-height=\"1009\" data-file-width=\"1991\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"111\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/0317_-_Milano_-_San_Calimero_-_Foto_Giovanni_Dall%27Orto_5-May-2007.jpg/220px-0317_-_Milano_-_San_Calimero_-_Foto_Giovanni_Dall%27Orto_5-May-2007.jpg\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/0317_-_Milano_-_San_Calimero_-_Foto_Giovanni_Dall%27Orto_5-May-2007.jpg/330px-0317_-_Milano_-_San_Calimero_-_Foto_Giovanni_Dall%27Orto_5-May-2007.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/0317_-_Milano_-_San_Calimero_-_Foto_Giovanni_Dall%27Orto_5-May-2007.jpg/440px-0317_-_Milano_-_San_Calimero_-_Foto_Giovanni_Dall%27Orto_5-May-2007.jpg 2x\" width=\"220\"/>\n        </a>\n        <div class=\"thumbcaption\">\n         <div class=\"magnify\">\n          <a class=\"internal\" href=\"/wiki/File:0317_-_Milano_-_San_Calimero_-_Foto_Giovanni_Dall%27Orto_5-May-2007.jpg\" title=\"Enlarge\">\n          </a>\n         </div>\n         A bust of\n         <i>\n          Erlembaldus Cotta\n         </i>\n         in the\n         <a class=\"new\" href=\"/w/index.php?title=Basilica_of_San_Calimero&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" title=\"Basilica of San Calimero (page does not exist)\">\n          Basilica of San Calimero\n         </a>\n         in Milan\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n      <p>\n       Saint\n       <b>\n        Erlembald\n       </b>\n       (or\n       <b>\n        Erlembaldo Cotta\n       </b>\n       ) (\n       <i>\n        Sanctus Herlembaldus\n       </i>\n       in\n       <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/Latin_language\" title=\"Latin language\">\n        Latin\n       </a>\n       ) (died 15 April 1075) was the political and military leader of the movement known as the\n       <i>\n        <a href=\"/wiki/Pataria\" title=\"Pataria\">\n         pataria\n        </a>\n       </i>\n       in\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Milan\" title=\"Milan\">\n        Milan\n       </a>\n       , a movement to reform the clergy and the church in the\n       <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/Archbishop_of_Milan\" title=\"Archbishop of Milan\">\n        Ambrosian diocese\n       </a>\n       .\n      </p>\n      <h2>\n       <span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Biography\">\n        Biography\n       </span>\n       <span class=\"mw-editsection\">\n        <span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">\n         [\n        </span>\n        <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Erlembald&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Biography\">\n         edit\n        </a>\n        <span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">\n         ]\n        </span>\n       </span>\n      </h2>\n      <p>\n       He was the brother of\n       <a class=\"new\" href=\"/w/index.php?title=Landolfo_Cotta&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" title=\"Landolfo Cotta (page does not exist)\">\n        Landulf\n       </a>\n       ,\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Subdeacon\" title=\"Subdeacon\">\n        subdeacon\n       </a>\n       of Milan. They were of the Cotta, a family of\n       <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/Valvassor\" title=\"Valvassor\">\n        valvassores\n       </a>\n       and vassals of the archdiocese. In his early career, Erlembald was referred to as a \"captain.\" In 1063, he returned from a pilgrimage to the\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Holy_Land\" title=\"Holy Land\">\n        Holy Land\n       </a>\n       and intended to become a monk when the deacon\n       <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/Ariald\" title=\"Ariald\">\n        Ariald\n       </a>\n       convinced him to take his brother's place at the head of the\n       <i>\n        pataria\n       </i>\n       . Erlembald, however, was not a cleric, but a soldier.\n      </p>\n      <p>\n       In 1064, he travelled to\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Rome\" title=\"Rome\">\n        Rome\n       </a>\n       to confer with\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Pope_Alexander_II\" title=\"Pope Alexander II\">\n        Pope Alexander II\n       </a>\n       and confirm his support. On his return to Milan, he revealed the change in the character of the\n       <i>\n        pataria\n       </i>\n       by living in a palace near the church of Saint Victor and the Forty Martyrs. With papal permission he began imposing his will by force on the clergy, by deposing abbots and proceeding against the bishop,\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Guido_da_Velate\" title=\"Guido da Velate\">\n        Guido da Velate\n       </a>\n       . Guido was first accused of taking false oaths for not acting against\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Simony\" title=\"Simony\">\n        simony\n       </a>\n       in his province. Guido, however, organised a resistance to the\n       <i>\n        patarini\n       </i>\n       . Because of this, Ariald imposed the interdict on the city during the feast of the\n       <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/Ascension_of_Jesus_Christ\" title=\"Ascension of Jesus Christ\">\n        Ascension\n       </a>\n       . The populace turned against him and he fled to\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Pavia\" title=\"Pavia\">\n        Pavia\n       </a>\n       . After being captured en route to Rome, Ariald was executed and his body thrown in\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Lake_Maggiore\" title=\"Lake Maggiore\">\n        Lake Maggiore\n       </a>\n       . On 3 May 1067, Erlembald recovered his body and reburied it in S. Celso in Milan on 17 May. Ariald's popularity was also recovered after the lifting of the interdict. A papal legation lent Erlembald much needed moral support at a congregation at\n       <a class=\"new\" href=\"/w/index.php?title=Vallambrosa&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" title=\"Vallambrosa (page does not exist)\">\n        Vallambrosa\n       </a>\n       .\n      </p>\n      <p>\n       In 1069, Guido renounced the see to\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Gotofredo_da_Castiglione\" title=\"Gotofredo da Castiglione\">\n        Gotofredo da Castiglione\n       </a>\n       with the support of the\n       <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/Emperor_Henry_IV\" title=\"Emperor Henry IV\">\n        Emperor Henry IV\n       </a>\n       . Gotofredo was immediately besieged in his castle. On 7 March 1070, violence broke out again in Milan and Gotofredo was arrested. That year, Guido request his archbishopric back from Erlembald. He was refused, but the\n       <i>\n        patarino\n       </i>\n       leader put him in S. Celso and then in the see of\n       <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/Bergoglio\" title=\"Bergoglio\">\n        Bergoglio\n       </a>\n       . On 6 January 1072, Erlembald appointed\n       <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/Atto,_Archbishop_of_Milan\" title=\"Atto, Archbishop of Milan\">\n        Atto\n       </a>\n       archbishop in opposition to the arrested Gotofredo. Strong opposition from the German court evaporated suddenly in 1073 when Henry was troubled by revolts in\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Saxony\" title=\"Saxony\">\n        Saxony\n       </a>\n       and had to ceded his rights in Milan to\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Pope_Gregory_VII\" title=\"Pope Gregory VII\">\n        Pope Gregory VII\n       </a>\n       . Gregory confirmed Atto and lent his support to Erlembald.\n      </p>\n      <p>\n       At this, the height of his power, an unfortunate fire broke out in the city and was interpreted as divine punishment for supporting the controversial\n       <i>\n        pataria\n       </i>\n       . The opposition factions in Milan signed a pact against Erlembald. He put down the revolt, but was killed in the battle and buried in S. Celso. From 6 to 26 May in 1095,\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Pope_Urban_II\" title=\"Pope Urban II\">\n        Pope Urban II\n       </a>\n       was present at Milan for the transferral of the relics of the canonised Erlembald to S. Dionigi. He was already a propaganda tool at the time of the preaching of the\n       <a href=\"/wiki/First_Crusade\" title=\"First Crusade\">\n        First Crusade\n       </a>\n       . He was translated once more in 1528 to the\n       <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/Duomo_of_Milan\" title=\"Duomo of Milan\">\n        Duomo\n       </a>\n       . His feast day is 27 July.\n      </p>\n      <h2>\n       <span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">\n        See also\n       </span>\n       <span class=\"mw-editsection\">\n        <span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">\n         [\n        </span>\n        <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Erlembald&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">\n         edit\n        </a>\n        <span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">\n         ]\n        </span>\n       </span>\n      </h2>\n      <div aria-label=\"Portals\" class=\"noprint metadata navbox\" role=\"navigation\" style=\"font-weight:bold;padding:0.4em 2em\">\n       <ul style=\"margin:0.1em 0 0\">\n        <li style=\"display:inline\">\n         <span style=\"display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap\">\n          <span style=\"margin:0 0.5em\">\n           <a class=\"image\" href=\"/wiki/File:P_vip.svg\">\n            <img alt=\"P vip.svg\" data-file-height=\"1944\" data-file-width=\"1911\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"21\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/69/P_vip.svg/21px-P_vip.svg.png\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/69/P_vip.svg/31px-P_vip.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/69/P_vip.svg/41px-P_vip.svg.png 2x\" width=\"21\"/>\n           </a>\n          </span>\n          <a href=\"/wiki/Portal:Biography\" title=\"Portal:Biography\">\n           Biography portal\n          </a>\n         </span>\n        </li>\n        <li style=\"display:inline\">\n         <span style=\"display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap\">\n          <span style=\"margin:0 0.5em\">\n           <a class=\"image\" href=\"/wiki/File:046CupolaSPietro.jpg\">\n            <img alt=\"046CupolaSPietro.jpg\" data-file-height=\"600\" data-file-width=\"800\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"18\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/046CupolaSPietro.jpg/24px-046CupolaSPietro.jpg\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/046CupolaSPietro.jpg/36px-046CupolaSPietro.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/046CupolaSPietro.jpg/48px-046CupolaSPietro.jpg 2x\" width=\"24\"/>\n           </a>\n          </span>\n          <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/Portal:Catholicism\" title=\"Portal:Catholicism\">\n           Catholicism portal\n          </a>\n         </span>\n        </li>\n        <li style=\"display:inline\">\n         <span style=\"display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap\">\n          <span style=\"margin:0 0.5em\">\n           <a class=\"image\" href=\"/wiki/File:Gloriole_blur.svg\">\n            <img alt=\"Gloriole blur.svg\" data-file-height=\"28\" data-file-width=\"32\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"21\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Gloriole_blur.svg/24px-Gloriole_blur.svg.png\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Gloriole_blur.svg/36p